{
  "text": "Adenovirus infection and propagation. Ad-LacZ, Ad-GFP, Ad-p53, and Ad-BRCA1 have been described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Ad-AntisenseBRCA1 was developed by subcloning a KpnI/XhoI fragment of BRCA1 (amino acids 1 to 500) [BRCA1(1-500)] from pCR3-BRCA1(1-500) into pAdTrack-CMV (15) . pAdTrack-BRCA1(1-500) was cotransformed into BJ5183 bacteria with pAdEasy to obtain a homologously recombined pAd-BRCA1(1-500) vector. This vector was transfected into 293 cells for the production of viral plaques. Adenoviruses expressing truncated BRCA1 were purified from 293 cells over a CsCl gradient and stored in a glycerol buffer [CITATION_4] . Viruses were propagated, their titers were determined, and they were amplified as described previously [CITATION_5] .",
